<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1631,1657]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[322,529,1631,1657]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref76348" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 a) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Five new species and additional records from the Far East. Kontyu, Tokyo, 56, 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara (1988a)</bibRefCitation>
gave a collection record of 
<specimenCount box="[840,963,1631,1658]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen from 
<collectingRegion box="[1143,1318,1631,1657]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
(Tedjuche = Dal’negorsk district) and no additional specimens have been available from the continent. The species is uncommon throughout its distribution range. The larvae are gregarious leaf rollers on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shinohara &amp; Hara 1993)" baseAuthorityName="Shinohara &amp; Hara" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[1038,1397,1703,1730]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1038,1102,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Alnus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H." box="[1116,1389,1703,1730]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="546" refId="ref77516" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H. (1993) Larvae of Pamphilius alnicola (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae), gregarious leaf-rollers on Alnus hirsuta. Japanese Journal of Entomology, Tokyo, 61, 546." type="journal article" year="1993">Shinohara &amp; Hara 1993</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,1523,2017]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
This is a member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linne" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[464,600,1739,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvaticus">
<emphasis box="[464,600,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. sylvaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[685,877,1739,1766]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="323 - 351" refId="ref76025" refString="Shinohara, A. (1985 a) Web-spinning sawflies of the sylvaticus group of Pamphilius (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Systematic Entomology, 10, 323 - 351. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1985. tb 00141. x" type="journal article" year="1985">
Shinohara 1985 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[864,877,1739,1766]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref76348" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 a) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Five new species and additional records from the Far East. Kontyu, Tokyo, 56, 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="1988">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1988 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[946,1028,1739,1765]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="99 - 116" refId="ref76721" refString="Shinohara, A. (2001) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Two new species, new collection records, and a key to Palearctic species. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 7, 99 - 116." type="journal article" year="2001">a, 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1038,1112,1739,1765]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">2002b</bibRefCitation>
). The maximum intraspecific 
<emphasis box="[151,165,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">p</emphasis>
-distance within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ermolenko" authorityYear="1973" box="[354,475,1775,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnicola">
<emphasis box="[354,475,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 0.5% in COI (n=2) and 0.1% in NaK (n=2). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ermolenko" authorityYear="1973" box="[1018,1245,1775,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnicola">
<emphasis box="[1018,1245,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Pamphilius alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retrieved as the sister of 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1985" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[290,621,1811,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[290,427,1812,1837]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. montanus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1985
</taxonomicName>
, with UFBoot support of 82% in the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1250,1811,1838]" captionStart="FIGURE 145" captionStartId="232.[151,250,1669,1693]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-26@232.[151,1436,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="232" captionText="FIGURE 145. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sylvaticus group, part 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876851/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 145</figureCitation>
), whereas it was retrieved as the sister of the clade consisting of 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1985" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[688,982,1847,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benesi">
<emphasis box="[688,788,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. benesi</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1985
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1988" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[994,1307,1847,1873]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[994,1112,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. pallidus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1988
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volatilis">
<emphasis box="[1318,1436,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. volatilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, F." box="[159,303,1883,1909]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="373 - 409" refId="ref79508" refString="Smith, F. (1874) Descriptions of new species of Tenthredinidae, Ichneumonidae, Chrysididae, Formicidae &amp; c. of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London for the Year, 1874, 373 - 409. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00867. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Smith, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1985" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[323,634,1883,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[323,438,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. gracilis</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1985
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara &amp; Kramp &amp; Taeger, 2022" authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Kramp &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2022" box="[647,801,1883,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciloides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[647,801,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. graciloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,901,1883,1909]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,901,1883,1909]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[958,1096,1884,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[958,1096,1884,1909]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with UFBoot support of 99% in the NaK tree (
<figureCitation box="[342,442,1919,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 159" captionStartId="244.[151,250,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,187,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-26@244.[151,1436,181,1733]" captionTargetPageId="244" captionText="FIGURE 159. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sylvaticus group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876882/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 159</figureCitation>
). In the distance data, the nearest neighbour of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ermolenko" authorityYear="1973" box="[980,1100,1919,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnicola">
<emphasis box="[980,1100,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1160,1278,1919,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volatilis">
<emphasis box="[1160,1278,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. volatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 4.9% in the COI analysis and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[653,790,1956,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[653,790,1956,1981]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[844,962,1955,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volatilis">
<emphasis box="[844,962,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. volatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a minimum of 0.6% in the NaK analysis.
</paragraph>
